# DaggerheartGM

A GM tool for the Daggerheart tabletop RPG. Built as a Node.js/Express server that serves a self-contained SPA.

## Architecture

- `server.js` ‚Äî Express server entry point. Serves static files from `public/` and falls back to `public/index.html` for any unmatched route (standard SPA behavior). API routes live here. On startup, runs DB migrations if `DATABASE_URL` is set. Includes a `GET /livereload` SSE endpoint that watches `public/` via `fs.watch` and broadcasts a `reload` event to all connected browsers when files change (used for dev hot-reload).
- `src/client/app.jsx` ‚Äî React SPA entry point. Imports from `./lib/api.js`, mounts via `ReactDOM.createRoot`. Manages top-level state (data, collectionMeta, activeElements, user). Uses `useRouter()` from `./lib/router.js` to derive the active view from the URL; all navigation calls `navigate()` so the browser back/forward buttons work. The nav bar user menu (click your name/email) provides Export JSON, Import JSON, and Sign Out. Persists `whiteboardEmbed`, `rolzRoomName`, `rolzUsername`, and `rolzPassword` in the `table_state` collection alongside `activeElements`. Data loading is lazy and per-collection: on auth only `table_state` and non-paginated collections (groups/scenes/adventures) load; adversaries/environments load on demand per active tab with pagination. `addToTable`/`startScene` use `POST /api/data/resolve` with `adopt: true` for scene/group/adventure expansion (auto-cloning all referenced adversaries/environments into the user's library). Direct adversary/environment Add to Table calls `cloneItemToLibrary(..., { play: true })` for non-own items or `recordPlay` for own items.
- `src/client/components/` ‚Äî UI components: `LibraryView.jsx`, `GMTableView.jsx`, `NavBtn.jsx`, `ItemCard.jsx`, `ItemDetailView.jsx`, `RolzRoomLog.jsx`. `LibraryView` has a compact/spacious view toggle (persisted to `localStorage` under `libraryViewMode`); compact mode uses a 7-column grid, smaller text/padding, hides the banner image, and shows a small bottom-right thumbnail that expands on hover. `ItemCard` accepts a `compact` boolean prop to switch between the two layouts. `GMTableView` has "Add Adversary / Environment / Group / Start Scene" buttons that open an `AddToTableModal` ‚Äî a vertical modal with its own independent filter state (source, tier, role/type, search) that fetches directly from the API; results display as text rows (Name, Tier, Role/Type). This modal state is fully isolated from the library tab filters.
- `src/client/components/forms/` ‚Äî Item creation/edit forms: `AdversaryForm`, `EnvironmentForm`, `GroupForm`, `SceneForm`, `AdventureForm`, plus shared inputs `ExperiencesInput`, `FeaturesInput`, `FormRow`, `MultiSelectRef`. Also `FeatureLibrary.jsx` ‚Äî a sidebar panel rendered inside `AdversaryForm`/`EnvironmentForm` (when `allItems` prop is provided) that shows deduplicated features from same-tier, same-subtype items sorted by source (own/srd/public/fcg), with hover-to-detail and click-to-add. Has an "Include Fresh Cut Grass" checkbox (default off) that self-fetches from `GET /api/fcg-search`.
- `src/client/components/modals/` ‚Äî Import modals: `RolzImportModal.jsx`. Shared utilities in `ImportModalShell.jsx` and `ImportPreviewCard.jsx`. Inline editing modals: `EditChoiceDialog.jsx` (asks "Edit Copy" vs "Edit Library Original"), `EditFormModal.jsx` (modal wrapper around `AdversaryForm`/`EnvironmentForm`).
- `src/client/lib/` ‚Äî Client-side utilities: `api.js` (Firebase init + fetch helpers + `loadCollection`, `loadTableState`, `resolveItems`, `cloneItemToLibrary`, `recordPlay`, `loadFcgSearch`, `postRolzRoll`, `fetchRolzRoomLog`), `helpers.js` (`generateId`), `constants.js`, `rolz-parser.js`, `rolz-export.js`, `router.js` (History API router: `useRouter()` hook + `parseRoute()`).
- `src/db.js` ‚Äî Postgres connection pool, migration runner, and query helpers. Exports `SRD_USER_ID = '__SRD__'` and `MIRROR_USER_ID = '__MIRROR__'`. Own-item helpers: `getItems`, `getItemsPaginated`, `countItems`. Unified community helpers (SRD + public + mirrors sorted by popularity): `countCommunityItems`, `getCommunityItemsPaginated`. Legacy unpaginated helpers: `getSrdItems`, `getPublicItems`. Popularity helpers: `incrementCloneCount`, `incrementPlayCount`, `upsertMirror`, `findAutoClone`. Mirror lookup: `getMirrorIds`. Other: `upsertItem`, `deleteItem`, `getItemsByIds`.
- `src/fcg-search.js` ‚Äî FreshCutGrass.app public search API integration. Exports `searchFCG({ search, tier, collection, limit, offset })`. Calls `https://freshcutgrass.app/api/adversaries/public/search`, classifies items by `type.startsWith("Environment")` (not tags), and translates to native format. Tagged `_source: 'fcg'` with `id` prefixed `fcg-`.
- `src/input.css` ‚Äî Tailwind CSS entry point (`@import "tailwindcss"`). Tailwind v4 scans `public/**/*.{html,jsx}` and `src/client/**/*.jsx` automatically.
- `migrations/` ‚Äî Numbered `.sql` migration files (e.g. `001_create_items_table.sql`). Applied automatically at startup via `src/db.js`. Add new files here to evolve the schema. `002_add_is_public.sql` adds the `is_public BOOLEAN` column. `003_add_popularity.sql` adds `clone_count` and `play_count` INTEGER columns and a `_clonedFrom` expression index.
- `scripts/fetch-srd.js` ‚Äî Fetches pre-built adversary/environment JSON from `seansbox/daggerheart-srd` on GitHub, transforms to app schema, writes to `data/srd-adversaries.json` and `data/srd-environments.json`. Run with `npm run fetch:srd`.
- `scripts/seed-srd.js` ‚Äî Reads `data/srd-*.json` and upserts them into the DB with `user_id='__SRD__'` and `is_public=true`. Run with `npm run seed:srd`.
- `data/` ‚Äî Generated JSON output from `scripts/fetch-srd.js`. Not committed to git.
- `public/index.html` ‚Äî Thin HTML shell. Links to the locally-built `public/styles.css`, loads Babel standalone and an ES importmap (pointing to esm.sh CDN for React 18, Firebase 10, Lucide React). Loads the app via `<script type="module" src="/app.js">`. Contains an inline `EventSource` script that connects to `/livereload` and calls `location.reload()` on `reload` events or on reconnect after the server restarts.
- `public/styles.css` ‚Äî Generated Tailwind CSS output. Do **not** edit by hand; rebuild with `npm run build:css`.
- `public/` ‚Äî All static assets (images, fonts, compiled JS, etc.) go here.
- `package.json` ‚Äî Uses ES modules (`"type": "module"`). Dependencies: `express`, `pg`, `firebase-admin`. Dev dependencies: `tailwindcss`, `@tailwindcss/cli`.

## Database

Supabase Postgres (or any Postgres). Set `DATABASE_URL` in `.env` to the connection string (URI format). Migrations run automatically on server start.

Schema uses a single `items` table:
- `(app_id, collection, id)` ‚Äî composite primary key
- `user_id` ‚Äî Firebase UID; all queries are scoped per user. Special values: `__SRD__` for SRD content, `__MIRROR__` for cached copies of external (FCG, etc.) items used for local-first search and popularity tracking.
- `data` ‚Äî JSONB blob storing the full entity. Auto-clones carry a `_clonedFrom` field pointing to the source item ID.
- `app_id` ‚Äî from `APP_ID` env var; namespaces data per deployment
- `is_public` ‚Äî boolean; when true, item is visible to all authenticated users (always true for SRD items)
- `clone_count` ‚Äî integer; incremented each time a new user clone is created from this item
- `play_count` ‚Äî integer; incremented each time this item (or a clone of it) is added to the GM Table
- `popularity` ‚Äî virtual/computed field returned by API: `clone_count + play_count` (formula is server-side to allow future reweighting)

## API Routes

- `GET /api/config` ‚Äî Returns `{ firebaseConfig }` (no auth required). Consumed by `app.jsx` at startup.
- `GET /api/data` ‚Äî Legacy bulk endpoint. Returns `{ adversaries, environments, groups, scenes, adventures, table_state }` for the authenticated user. Supports `includeSrd=1` and `includePublic=1`. Kept for backwards compatibility.
- `GET /api/data/:collection` ‚Äî **Primary read endpoint.** Paginated per-collection fetch. Params: `offset` (default 0), `limit` (default 20, max 100), `includeSrd=1`, `includePublic=1`, `includeFcg=1`, `search`. Returns `{ items, totalCount, dbCount }`. Source priority: own (by popularity) ‚Üí community/SRD/public/mirrors (by popularity) ‚Üí FCG live results (deduped against mirrors). Each item includes `clone_count`, `play_count`, and `popularity`. `table_state` returns the single record without pagination. FCG items tagged `_source: 'fcg'`.
- `POST /api/data/resolve` ‚Äî Batch resolve items by ID across collections. Body: `{ adversaries?, environments?, groups?, scenes?, adopt?: boolean }`. Returns matching items from DB. When `adopt: true`, non-own adversaries/environments are auto-cloned into the caller's library (find-or-create via `_clonedFrom`) and popularity counts are incremented; returns clones in place of originals.
- `POST /api/data/:collection/clone` ‚Äî Clone an item into the user's library. Body: `{ source, play: boolean }`. `play=false`: always creates a new copy (explicit Clone button), increments `clone_count` on source. `play=true`: finds an existing auto-clone (matched by `_clonedFrom`) and reuses it, or creates one; increments `clone_count` (new clone only) and `play_count` on source. For external sources (FCG etc.), upserts a `__MIRROR__` row. Returns `{ item }` ‚Äî the user's owned clone.
- `POST /api/data/:collection/play` ‚Äî Record a play of an own item. Body: `{ itemId }`. Increments `play_count`. Returns `{ ok: true }`.
- `PUT /api/data/:collection` ‚Äî Upsert an item (body is the item JSON). Respects `is_public` field. Returns the saved item.
- `DELETE /api/data/:collection/:id` ‚Äî Delete an item.
- `GET /api/fcg-search?search=&tier=` ‚Äî Requires auth. Lightweight endpoint for the Feature Library FCG toggle. Calls the FCG public search API and returns `{ adversaries, environments }` with no DB queries.
- `GET /livereload` ‚Äî SSE endpoint (no auth). Watches `public/` for changes via `fs.watch` (debounced 150 ms) and sends `data: reload` to all connected browsers. The browser client reconnects automatically after a server restart and reloads on reconnect. Used exclusively for dev live-reload.
- `GET /api/rolz-roomlog?room=NAME` ‚Äî Requires auth. Proxies the Rolz room log feed (`https://rolz.org/api/roomlog`). Returns `{ room, items }` with message history. Polled by `RolzRoomLog` component every 5 seconds.
- `POST /api/rolz-post` ‚Äî Requires auth. Body: `{ room, text, from, rolzUsername, rolzPassword }`. Logs into Rolz.org with the provided credentials (server-side session cache keyed by Firebase UID, TTL 30 min), then proxies the roll post to `https://rolz.org/api/post` with the session cookie forwarded. On "Invalid account name" response, invalidates the cache and retries once with a fresh login. Returns the Rolz JSON response.

All `/api/data` routes require an `Authorization: Bearer <Firebase ID token>` header. The server verifies the token via `firebase-admin` (uses `FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`; no service account key needed).

